To THE BANDUSIAN FouNTAiN.

The site of this fountain has been a matter of controversy, interesting to those who seek to ascertain the localities of places endeared to them by the poets. Acron and others assumed it to be in the neighbourhood of Horace's' Sabine home, and identify it with the rivulet of Digentia (Licenza).
